==English==
n. 
(1) One who cures or who professes to cure disease: usually employed in a somewhat contemptuous sense and in composition; as, mind-curist, sure-curist, etc. (really formed from mind-cure + -ist, etc.).
(2) One who curates (where "cur" is stemmed from "curation").

